that I do not need them to read. I have several reasons:

1) lack of time with all other seniors

2) senior are very confident in their English, and they feel that they can do anything. But I have to tell them, unfortunately, nowadays, most companies still do not accept Arabs English unless if they read and write well. And this is why I decided to do as a first step of a growth in my students’ level, that they should read more, not just write in their compositions.

I go this way: after planning a sequence which starts with identifying the main points of the story (in my case, story is from Alain Robbe-Grillet on one of his stories (title is taken from Wikipedia))

At first I give an inf101 sheets (equal to the original), asking them to read it three times at the same time asking them to focus more on the structure. At the end, they should submit the form.

Second, I ask all to work read the passage once without looking to the inf101, just in case if they could not understand it, because of its tone mix with grown-ups’ casual speech.

Third inf101. I ask to fill it once again, and I show it to the whole class.

Finally, I ask them to make a table responding to my questions, and I will give them the sequence of the answers after completing it.
